een performers and audiences in the Prison Monologues. Blending ethnography, literary studies, psychological analysis, and criminal justice critique, Trapedo Sims centers the often-overlooked stories of incarcerated Native Hawaiian and Pacific Islander women in Hawai‘i in ways that resound with the broader American narrative: the disproportionate incarceration of people of color in the prison-industrial complex.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aAmerican literaturexHistory and criticismy21st centuryzHawaii. 0aAmerican literaturexWomen authorszHawaii. 0aPrisoners' writings, AmericanxHistory and criticismzHawaii. 0aWomen prisonerszHawaii. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Gender Studies.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311099775008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Cultural and Area Studies 2023 Englishz978311131909408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Cultural and Area Studies 2023z978311131812740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478027362?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478027362423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781478027362/original  a978-3-11-099775-0  Duke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131812-7  EBOOK PACKAGE Cultural and Area Studies 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131909-4  EBOOK PACKAGE Cultural and Area Studies 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb2023  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2023